data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — no longer accepts expression trees

The `setters` parameter changed from `Expression<Func<...>>` to `Func<...>`. Your manual expression tree code **won't compile**.

**Fix** — use a regular lambda with imperative logic:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

### 2. Complex type columns — naming changes (two issues)

**a) Same-named properties are now uniquified.** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one column; now they get `Street` and `Street1`. To keep the old behavior, pin column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**b) Nested complex types now use the full path.** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` was column `BillingAddress_City`; now it's `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To preserve the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

> **Important:** If you have existing migrations/data, either pin all old column names or generate a new migration (which will rename columns).

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter for redacted SQL logging.

**Fix** — add the parameter to your implementation:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)          // ← new parameter
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
